ğŸš€ How to Run the Project

Open the Jupyter notebook:

jupyter notebook wrangle_act.ipynb


Follow the workflow inside the notebook:

Gather data: Import the datasets (twitter_archive_enhanced.csv, image_predictions.tsv, and tweet_json-copy.txt).

Assess data: Identify quality and tidiness issues.

Clean data: Apply programmatic cleaning using Pandas.

Store cleaned data: Export the cleaned dataset as twitter_archive_master.csv.

Analyze and visualize: Explore patterns and create summary statistics and charts.

ğŸ“ˆ Key Steps in the Project

Data Gathering

Loaded three datasets from different sources and formats (CSV, TSV, JSON).

Data Assessment

Detected quality issues (missing data, inconsistent names, invalid ratings).

Identified tidiness issues (dog stages spread across multiple columns).

Data Cleaning

Fixed column names, removed duplicates, standardized formats.

Merged datasets into one clean master file.

Analysis and Visualization

Explored tweet popularity, dog ratings, and image prediction results.

Visualized trends in ratings, retweets, and favorites.

